<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Endemic to the southern part of the Baja California peninsular, where it grows in low deciduous forest at around 400 m.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">MEXICO. Baja California Sur</emphasis>
: one mile W of San Antonio, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B.J. Hammerly</emphasis>
416 (CAS, US); Sierra San Francisquito, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T.S. Brandegee</emphasis>
Oct 1 1899 (US); El Palmiar Canyon, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R.M. Turner &amp; C.H. Lowe</emphasis>
59-138 (ARIZ); 3 km al N. del Poblado La Huerta, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
M. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Domínguez-L">Dominguez-L</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
. 3526 (ARIZ, HCIB).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
